inary until it's threatened. Then it becomes infinitely precious.\n\n- Lynda Williams, Holy war\n|\nSmartass Disciple: Master, I believe that the truth will prevail at the end.Master of Stupidity: No 'the end' for the truth. 'Prevail' is something else.\n\n- Toba Beta, Betelgeuse Incident: Insiden Bait Al-Jauza\n|\nWhat matters creative endless toil, When, at a snatch, oblivion ends the coil?\n\n- Johann Wolfgang von Goethe, Faust: Der Tragödie erster und zweiter Teil. Urfaust\n|\nKeeping score, in friendships, is a losing game.\n\n- Frank Sonnenberg, BookSmart: Hundreds of real-world lessons for success and happiness\n|\nFar greater than all the material possessions that I possess, is my Freedom to Choose, my Freedom to Live, and my Freedom to be Happy.\n\n- RVM\n|\nThat’s the attractive thing about war,” said Rosewater. “Absolutely everybody gets a little something.\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., Slaughterhouse-Five\n|\nNobody will walk the entire journey with you. Their roads do diverge, so does yours.\n\n- Damini Aggarwal, Zindagi Rewind\n|\nMost people are full of themselves and speak only the obnoxiously superficial, in other words they're annoying as hell\n\n- Novala Takemoto, Missin' (Novel)\n|\nI noticed you made a bee-line for their bookcases.' It is the oldest and most incorrigible trait of the book-lover.\n\n- Paul  Collins, Sixpence House: Lost in a Town of Books\n|\nThe naysayer has a place in your life, but if that is someone that you are considering to be your friend, do they truly add value in your life?\n\n- Dee-Williams\n|\nUltimately, we are all dead men - we only become born again after we have discovered our purpose, a reason to live.\n\n- Kabelo\n|\nSimply put, self-centered and egocentric people don'tinspire others. We are inspired by people who placeothers-- other people, other ideas, other goals-- abovethemselves.\n\n- Del Suggs, Truly Leading: Lessons in Leadership\n|\nThey say that somewhere in Africa the elephants have a secret grave where they